BIB                 12         28
TITLE      Expanding the isotopic frontier: seven new
           neutron-rich rare-earth isotopes observed at RIKEN RI
           beam factory
AUTHOR     (T.Sumikama, N.Fukuda, T.Kubo, H.Suzuki, H.Takeda,
            N.Inabe, D.Kameda, D.S.Ahn, D.Murai, K.Yoshida,
            K.Kusaka, Y.Yanagisawa, M.Ohtake, Y.Shimizu, Y.Sato,
            H.Sato, H.Otsu, H.Baba, G.Lorusso, P.-A.Soderstrom,
            T.Isobe, N.Imai, M.Mukai, S.Kimura, H.Miyatake,
            N.Iwasa, A.Yagi, R.Yokoyama, O.B.Tarasov, H.Geissel)
INSTITUTE  (2JPNIPC,2JPNYOK,2JPNTOK,2JPNKEK,2JPNTOH,2JPNOSA,
           1USAMSU,2GERGSI)
REFERENCE  (J,JPJ,95,024202,2026)
INC-SOURCE (FRAGM) Neutron-rich RI beams were produced via
                   in-flight fission by bombarding a beryllium
                   target with a 238U beam that was accelerated
                   to 345 MeV/nucleon.
SAMPLE     - Chemical-form of target is element.
           - Physical-form of target is solid.
METHOD     (TOFDE)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2JPNIPC) RIBF
DETECTOR   (MAGSP,SCIN) BigRIPS
           (IOCH)
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-1) The systematic uncertainty attributable to the
                   uncertainties in the primary beam intensity
                   and transport efficiency evaluation.
           (ERR-S) Statistical uncertainty
STATUS     (TABLE,,T.Sumikama+,J,JPJ,95,024202,2026) Table II
HISTORY    (20260226C) MA
ENDBIB              28
COMMON               2          3
EN         ERR-1
MEV/A      PER-CENT
 345.       50.
ENDCOMMON            3
